===Verb===
{{en-verb|talks down|talking down|talked down}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To [[negotiate]] a [[lower]] price.
#: ''If he offers a very high price, see if you can '''talk''' him '''down''' before you agree to anything.''
# {{lb|en|flying}} Of [[ground control]]: to verbally assist someone to land an aircraft.
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1960|month=Feb|title=Business with FAA|page=109|magazine=Flying Magazine|passage=GET TALKED DOWN: When a pilot gets caught in weather, he may call the nearest tower for Ground Controlled Approach landing assistance, wherever the airport has GCA radar.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2000|author=Larry King|title=Anything Goes!: What I've Learned from Pundits, Politicians, and Presidents|isbn=0759520356|page=139|passage=He got out, looked at me, and said, “I feel like Doris Day in Julie when she was '''talked down''' by air traffic control and landed the airplane.”[.]}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2008|author=Winston Fletcher|title=Powers of Persuasion: The Inside Story of British Advertising 1951-2000|isbn=0191647594|passage=Its Spielberg-inspired first commercial, in which Manhattan Island floated loftily through the sky and was '''talked down''' by air traffic control at Heathrow[.]}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2008|author=Nelson DeMille and Thomas Block|title=Mayday|isbn=0748109455|passage=In other words, if you '''talk''' him '''down''' and he crashes, you're worse off than if you hadn't tried.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To convince a person to cease a drastic action or response, such as a suicide attempt or act of rage.
#* 2007, [https://books.google.com/books?id=KmR6dmWMWeMC&pg=PT77&dq=talked+him+down&hl=en&sa=X&ei=cg2eVfTYDIzy-AGBvZC4BQ&ved=0CDsQ6AEwBQ ''Deep Storm''] by Lincoln Child
#*: '''Talk him down''', the rule book went. Calm him, get him secured. Easier said than done. Crane had '''talked down''' a would-be jumper standing on a support cable of the George Washington Bridge.
#* [https://books.google.com/books?id=P0A3SykTK6UC&pg=PA212&dq=talked+him+down&hl=en&sa=X&ei=MQ6eVaDdEsXAtQW8lLngBQ&ved=0CD8Q6AEwBjgK ''Shelby: A Great Love''] by CJ Raines
#*: And that guy that '''talked him down''' told us what happen{{SIC}}. It's kidnapping, attempted assault.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[overcome]] by [[spoken]] [[argument]].

